					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6245537#post-3852808</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6245537/scp-3956#post-3852808</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 27 Jun 2018 23:29:15 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TL333s</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1304786</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Note, I do not count the pun as a good thing. &lt;.&lt;</p> <p>And, I dunno. It's an anomaly that occurs during plays, in which weird things happen onstage and to the audience, and also a weird dude shows up. That may be overly reductive in the course of proving my point, admittedly, but the broad strokes are the same. The only real thing that makes this stand apart is the imagery and the fact that it's not fatal.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6245537#post-3852802</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6245537/scp-3956#post-3852802</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 27 Jun 2018 23:24:44 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>rubberchickenzilla</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3935783</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This was supped to focus more on the actor and his journey than the play itself (which is what the Hanged King is about, as I read it), though I do see where you're coming from. Any way I could make this more distinct for you?</p> <p>And thank you for picking up on the pun. I was worried it wasn't landing.</p> <p>EDIT: For anyone reading this who doesn't know, 'The Hanged King' is <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-701">SCP-701</a>, which is actually called 'The Hanged King's Tragedy'.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
