					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6245537#post-3852773</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6245537/scp-3956#post-3852773</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 27 Jun 2018 22:53:49 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zyn</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1404533</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>SCP-3956-2 approached Agent ██████, the sole observer of this event, once the show had ended. It handed him a program with the message, &quot;I've seen you at all my shows. Thank you for never giving up on me! - WORMS&quot; written inside along with several mealworms. It then placed its mouth against his hand and exited the lobby.</p> </blockquote> <p>So this is my favorite part of the article and I just found it so wonderfully charming in such a silly way.</p> <p>Solid +1 from me here; I liked it when I reviewed it, and I like it now.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
